      "You need to know the 'starting point' (Generation) and the 'long-distance' stage (Transmission)."
    ],
    "questionText": "List the three specific voltages used for the UK transmission network and identify five different generation methods from the taught range.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Transmission voltages: 132 kV, 275 kV, 400 kV",
      "Generation methods (any five): coal, oil, biomass, wind, wave, hydro, nuclear, photovoltaic, gas, micro-generation"
    ],
    "hint": "Transmission voltages are the three highest values in kV. For generation, think of fossil fuels, renewables, and nuclear options."
  }
